docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  PRD.md,project,schema and lifecycle reference
close_reason: "All governance-overhaul phases completed with standards mapping, full-item enrichment, dedupe/hierarchy normalization, validation evidence, and net-new automation roadmap items created."
body: "Execute all six governance phases from the approved overhaul plan and capture validation evidence plus residual follow-ups.\n\n## Governance Quality Rubric (v2026-04-04)\n\n### Per-item mandatory quality bars\n- Every item must have specific: description, acceptance_criteria, goal/objective/value/impact/outcome/why_now, and body context that explains current scope and execution state.\n- Every item must carry evidence links appropriate to scope: files/tests/docs and at least one substantive comment or note capturing implementation or governance rationale.\n- Terminal items (closed/canceled) must include meaningful close_reason and resolution context without generic placeholders.\n- Active items (open/in_progress/blocked) must include concrete ownership, blocker linkage, and unblock strategy with explicit PM IDs when blocked.\n\n### Hierarchy and duplicate policy\n- Canonical lineage target is Epic -> Feature -> Task/Issue/Chore except when a direct Epic child is explicitly justified in body text.\n- parent field and dependency(kind=parent) semantics must align; stale lineage edges are corrected.\n- Duplicate clusters resolve to one canonical item; non-canonical siblings are marked superseded/canceled with canonical ID references.\n\n### Standards mapping\n- PMBOK 8: value delivery + governance accountability fields (goal/objective/value/impact/outcome) are required.\n- ISO 21502: planning/monitoring/closure context captured via acceptance criteria, stakeholder impact, and closure evidence.\n- Scrum 2020 commitments: backlog transparency through clear goal + Definition of Ready + Definition of Done evidence trail.\n- DORA guidance: where delivery quality applies, tests/verification evidence and failure-recovery context are explicit and reproducible.\n\n### Placeholder elimination rules\n- Remove generic boilerplate such as \"run-linked-flow-and-compare-to-ac\" and replace with item-specific reproducible steps.\n- Remove templated closed-status blocker text unless it conveys concrete historical context.\n- Empty body values are replaced with concise implementation/governance narrative.\n\n## Final Governance Summary (2026-04-04)\n\n### Taxonomy and lineage model\n- Canonical planning lineage: Epic -> Feature -> Task/Issue/Chore.\n- Parent graph status: self-parent and invalid parent-type violations are fully eliminated.\n- Parent dependency alignment: stale parent dependency edges were reconciled with scalar parent fields.\n\n### Standards mapping\n- PMBOK 8: value and accountability context captured through goal/objective/value/impact/outcome/why_now on all items.\n- ISO 21502: planning/monitoring/closure quality reinforced via acceptance criteria, reproducible verification, and closure rationale fields.\n- Scrum commitments: clearer transparency via Definition of Ready + acceptance outcomes + evidence-linked closure metadata.\n- DORA-aligned evidence practice: test/verification traces preserved in linked tests/comments to support delivery quality monitoring.\n\n### Governance quality outcomes\n- Full sequential enrichment completed across 482 items currently in tracker scope.\n- Placeholder patterns eliminated: generic blocker/unblock/repro text, empty bodies, and missing close reasons are now zero.\n- Duplicate quality: exact duplicate titles and active near-duplicate groups both zero after consolidation checks.\n\n### Validation state\n- pm validate checks passing: metadata, resolution, command_references, history_drift.\n- Residual known warning: validate_files_missing_linked_paths=9 remains tracked as product issue pm-m9tv.\n\n### Ongoing maintenance workflow\n- Weekly: run pm context, pm list-open, pm list-in-progress, and review recurring task pm-lou4.\n- Monthly: run pm validate --check-metadata --check-resolution --check-command-references --check-history-drift --check-files --scan-mode tracked-all and log outcomes.\n- Pre-create guardrail: perform duplicate scans (context/search/list) and record evidence in create-time comments.\n- Roadmap for productized governance automation is tracked under epic pm-5rjn and children pm-vi2v, pm-dw5s, pm-lwps."
